# Patch for CVE-2026-53655
# Fix PAX header smuggling / tar interpretation-conflict in node-tar
#
# A PAX extended header (x/g) describes the *next file entry*, per POSIX pax,
# not the GNU long-name (L) / long-link (K) or further PAX (x/g) headers that
# may sit between it and that file. Header.decode previously applied the
# pending ex/gex overrides (notably size) to whatever header was decoded next,
# including those intermediary extension headers. A crafted stream ordered
# x(size=N) -> L -> file would advance the cursor by N for the L header
# instead of by L's true payload length, desynchronizing the parser relative
# to GNU tar, libarchive, Python tarfile and the Rust tar crates. This is a
# tar interpretation-conflict / file-smuggling primitive (CWE-436).
#
# Fix: only apply extended-header overrides to entries whose typeflag belongs
# to a new `normalFsTypes` allow-list of known filesystem entry types
# ('0','','1','2','3','4','5','6','7','D'). Intermediary L/K/x/g blocks no
# longer have ex/gex fields applied, so the parser advances by the block's
# own payload length and stays in sync with other tar implementations.
#
# This patch targets the published npm package's compiled dist/ files
# (commonjs + esm). The TypeScript change in upstream src/header.ts and
# src/types.ts is translated to the lowered JS form here:
#   * `as EntryTypeCode` cast is dropped (no types at runtime).
#   * The `normalFsTypes` Set is exported as `exports.normalFsTypes` for
#     commonjs and `export const normalFsTypes` for esm, matching how each
#     module already exports `name`/`code`.
#   * The typeflag decode `const t = decString(buf, off + 156, 1)` is moved
#     above the field decode, exactly as upstream; the duplicate decode that
#     used to live just before `if (types.isCode(t))` is removed.
#
# Affected version: tar@7.5.11
# Advisory: https://github.com/isaacs/node-tar/security/advisories/GHSA-vmf3-w455-68vh
# Upstream commit: https://github.com/isaacs/node-tar/commit/21a822027658c8063542be330530bbecdf0dbbfe

